      • matchingProducts

        @NonNull
public rx.Observable<FashionService.SearchResult> matchingProducts(@NonNull
                                                                            java.lang.String imageId,
                                                                            @NonNull
                                                                            java.io.File imageFile,
                                                                            @NonNull
                                                                            FashionService.SearchFilter filter)
        matching similar products by providing a image file the filter is provided here to support use cases that when user return back to a match result after certain time and the uploaded image has been expired, but user want to continue from that match result. for initial search pls just pass in a empty filter with location set.
        Parameters:
        imageId - a id client created to refer to the image file. it will be used in subsequent refining search
        imageFile - the reference image to send to the product matching service, pls make sure image dimension does not exceed IMAGE_MAXIMUM_DIMENSION
        filter - the filter to use.
        Returns:
        returns a rx.Observable object which will do the service call and pass the result to client. not null
        See Also:
        rx.Observable

      • matchingProducts

        @NonNull
public rx.Observable<FashionService.SearchResult> matchingProducts(@NonNull
                                                                            java.lang.String imageId,
                                                                            @NonNull
                                                                            java.lang.String url,
                                                                            @NonNull
                                                                            FashionService.SearchFilter filter)
        matching similar products by providing a image url the filter is provided here to support use cases that when user return back to a match result after certain time and the uploaded image has been expired, but user want to continue from that match result. for initial search pls just pass in a empty filter with location set.
        Parameters:
        imageId - a id client created to refer to the image file. it will be used in subsequent refining search
        url - a url pointing to the reference image from which product matching service will retrieve the image
        filter - the filter to use.
        Returns:
        returns a rx.Observable object which will do the service call and pass the result to client. not null
        See Also:
        rx.Observable
